## 11. Open hypotheses (ranked, post-Capture15)
1. **Dynamic INDEX buffer race** (never fixed; batcher uses it; same shared-ring arch). â† test first if serialization confirms a race.
2. **Map/Unmap â†’ draw ordering** on the dynamic VB for deferred-across-passes draws (a missing Flush/fence between the skinned write and its later-pass draw).
3. Per-object transform / every-other-frame skinning interaction producing a stale binding (less likely â€” stored data is clean & correct for the drawn mesh).
4. (Falsified) VB data corruption / buffer lifetime / ring contention â€” 5 fixes, all failed; Capture15 shows VB data clean.

