The render commands do use local indices across the whole mesh and pass the min/max range only as metadata; they do not remap indices down to zero. D3D9 handles that by keeping stream offset at zero and adding the dynamic ring slice offset to `BaseVertexIndex`; D3D11 currently bakes the slice offset into IA and keeps `BaseVertexLocation=0`, which is equivalent only if the IB indices remain local to the uploaded full mesh. That still matches your static arithmetic, so I’m not going to blame that by itself.
