# CONSULT-23 â€” Mechanism + minimal fix

## Executive summary

The 2026-06-06 probes change the diagnosis from the 2026-06-05 â€œcapture-invisible raceâ€ story. **Clean CPU skin + clean pre-`Unmap` slice + collapsed RenderDoc VB at draw + serialization dead + per-buffer isolation dead** narrows this to a **deterministic fetch/bind/accounting problem**, not â€œthe skin is wrongâ€ and not â€œfix the ring lifetime again.â€

The best-fit mechanism is a **two-part D3D11-only failure**:

1. **Ring accounting (`ms_used += requested` at lock, not actual at unlock)** creates bogus 2 MB reservations (CuiLayer) and a high discard rate that accidentally masks overlap.
2. **At draw time, the IA fetch does not read the same byte band that was written** â€” most likely **`ms_currentVBVectorOffsets[0]` at `applyPreDrawState` â‰  the slice written in `prepareToDraw`**, producing the signature **25 good verts then one repeated position for the tail**. That pattern is almost never â€œrandom GPU garbageâ€; it is **wrong base offset into the ring + tail reading a repeated-vertex writer (UI quad / fan / degenerate slice)**.

Per-buffer isolation failing is consistent with that: **if the bug is bind offset / path (vector vs single), giving the garment its own `ID3D11Buffer` does nothing.**

